name: Maine Coon
history: The Maine Coon is America's native longhaired cat and one of the oldest natural breeds in North America. Generally regarded as a native of the state of Maine, where it was made the official state cat in 1985. The breed developed through natural selection in the harsh New England climate, creating a hardy, handsome breed well equipped to survive hostile winters. Early Maine Coons were often polydactyls, believed to help them use their paws as 'natural snowshoes' during snowy Maine winters.

appearance.colors: Various (brown tabby, black, white, blue, red, etc.)

temperament.summary: Sweet-tempered, gentle, friendly, and social. They have a clown-like personality and are willing to 'help' their owners, yet aren't demanding of attention. They make excellent companions for large, active families and get along well with children, dogs, and other cats.

care.grooming: Weekly combing is usually sufficient to keep coat in top condition
care.exercise: Interactive toys provide exercise and bonding time; many play fetch
care.dietary_notes: High-quality diet; monitor portions to prevent obesity
care.nutrition: High-protein diet; monitor portions to prevent obesity

health.vaccinations: Core vaccines (FVRCP, rabies) per vet schedule

common_medications.name: Joint Supplement
common_medications.purpose: Supports joint health for large breeds
common_medications.usage_notes: Mix with food daily, as recommended by vet

veterinary_care_recommendations.parasite_prevention: Year-round flea, tick, and heartworm prevention
veterinary_care_recommendations.special_screenings: Cardiac ultrasound after age 3-4 to screen for HCM

genetic_precautions: Perform DNA tests for HCM and SMA genes before breeding
Avoid close inbreeding to maintain genetic diversity

other_traits: Known as the 'gentle giants' of the cat world; often enjoy water and have a soft chirping voice
fun_facts: Maine Coons are the only native longhaired American breed among pedigreed cats
They often chirp and trill rather than meow to communicate
Some Maine Coons have six toes (polydactyls) recognized by TICA
Most Maine Coons actually like water and are good swimmers
They don't reach full maturity until 4 years of age
Known as 'gentle giants' due to their size and friendly nature

name: Persian
history: One of the oldest cat breeds, the Persian has a long and illustrious history. Named after their country of origin, Persia (modern-day Iran), these cats were first imported to Europe in the 1600s. The breed was refined in Britain and later in America, developing the distinctive flat face and luxurious coat we know today.

temperament.summary: Calm, gentle, and sweet-natured. Persians are quiet, docile cats who prefer a serene environment. They are affectionate with their families but not overly demanding of attention.

care.grooming: Daily brushing required to prevent matting; regular eye cleaning needed
care.exercise: Minimal exercise needs; prefers calm indoor environment
care.nutrition: Premium diet with attention to coat health; regular feeding schedule

health.veterinary_recommendations: Regular health screenings, eye care, respiratory monitoring
health.vaccinations: Core vaccines (FVRCP, rabies) per vet schedule

common_medications.name: Eye drops
common_medications.purpose: Prevents eye infections and tear staining

veterinary_care_recommendations.dental_care: Regular dental cleaning due to facial structure
veterinary_care_recommendations.special_screenings: Regular kidney function tests; eye examinations

other_traits: Prefer quiet, stable environments; known for their regal appearance and calm demeanor
fun_facts: One of the most popular cat breeds worldwide
Featured in numerous movies and TV shows
Requires daily grooming to prevent matting
Come in over 80 color combinations
Known for their calm, gentle demeanor
Can live 12-17 years with proper care
